roles are used for RBAC. role binds aaocaite a role and user together. the relation is essentially this: What a role has access to and can do is in  defined in the role what, the role binding then asociates this role with user

RBAC is namespace scoped. 


N/B: you can us the `k auth can-i create <object>` to confirm if you have access to performing specific action. 

